page_analysis.text_content:
Attached garages/carports site planning

• Attached garages must comply with same setbacks as main dwelling.

Note: Uncovered spaces must be located beyond the required frontyard and beyond the first 10' of the street-side yard.

visual_elements.description: Three site planning examples showing different configurations for attached garages/carports on residential lots. Each example shows a bird's-eye view of a lot with buildings, setbacks, and parking arrangements. Includes a detailed key explaining all symbols and patterns used.

Figure 33 - Site planning solutions diagram with three scenarios: A) Interior lot with 1-car garage and uncovered space in sideyard, B) Interior lot with 1-car garage and uncovered space in driveway, C) Corner lot with 2-car garage and no uncovered spaces
